## Example 4 — Solve a Radical Equation

Solve:

`(2/3)(11x + 14)^(1/6) + 8 = 10`

Isolate the radical:

`(2/3)(11x + 14)^(1/6) = 2`

`(11x + 14)^(1/6) = 3`

Raise both sides to the sixth power:

`11x + 14 = 729`

`11x = 715`

`x = 65`

This value makes the equation true.

